{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_7","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \"team|mailbox|Loop 1m|10m|codexLoop|tab|board|resolveLiveThread|lastPayload\" src package.json .codex-loop task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md'","aggregated_output":"task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:11:Turn the current early mailbox prototype into a dependable `codex-loop`-driven team-coordination track without breaking existing single-thread, board, loop, or dashboard workflows.\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:15:- mailbox-backed multi-thread coordination under `.codex-team/`\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:17:- non-destructive UI surfacing for team state inside the existing dashboard\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:23:- [x] add new team-mode capabilities as opt-in enhancements, not replacements for current flows\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:24:- [x] do not regress existing thread lifecycle, board interactions, auto-continue, or loop controls\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:25:- [x] keep mailbox state isolated from legacy board/tab metadata so rollback stays easy\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:28:- [x] treat version safety as a standing gate: if a slice risks breaking the current stable behavior, stop expanding scope and steer the next loop toward rollback, isolation, or plan correction first\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:32:- [x] create and maintain one mailbox-specific task-plan as the long-form source of truth\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:34:- [x] align `.codex-loop/prompt.md` so recurring passes stay anchored to this mailbox track\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:38:## Task 2 — Mailbox Protocol Stabilization\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:40:- [x] define the minimal on-disk mailbox schema for `tasks/`, `events/`, `inbox/`, `agents/`, and `team.md`\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:43:- [x] make restart recovery rely on mailbox files instead of inferred free text\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:47:Mailbox root: `.codex-team/`\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:49:- `team-space.json`: workspace metadata with `team_id`, `workspace`, `created_at`, `protocol_version`, and `mode`.\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:50:- `team.md`: human-readable operating brief. It may hold shared goals, rules, and links, but it is not the structured task source of truth.\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:57:IDs should remain filename-safe. Structured writes should prefer `tasks/`, `events/`, `inbox/`, and `agents/` over parsing free text from `team.md`.\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:62:- [ ] support worker actions as mailbox events only: claim, heartbeat, blocked, complete\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:68:Current mailbox action boundaries:\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:70:- Supervisor actions are explicit host/dashboard actions: initialize team space, assign a task to a live thread, inspect mailbox-derived team state, recover by re-reading mailbox files on refresh, and receive handoffs through events plus supervisor inbox messages.\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:71:- Worker actions are represented as mailbox state transitions plus append-only events: claim, heartbeat/progress, blocked, and complete.\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:73:- This model does not route work through board tabs and does not replace legacy thread lifecycle state.\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:85:## Task 4 — Non-Destructive Dashboard Surface\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:87:- [x] surface mailbox summary in overview without reshaping existing overview cards\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:88:- [x] expose thread-level team controls only inside bounded surfaces such as the drawer\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:89:- [x] avoid overloading current board tab semantics with team routing semantics\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:90:- [x] make the team surface clearly secondary when mailbox mode is not initialized\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:97:- [x] ensure the default quick-start affordance reads as `Loop 1m` instead of `Loop 10m`\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:102:- [x] verify that opening the dashboard still works when no team space exists\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:103:- [x] verify that mailbox actions do not change legacy thread status unless explicitly intended\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:104:- [x] reject stale or non-existent thread ids before mailbox actions write `.codex-team` task or agent state, using `panel.lastPayload.dashboard.threads` as the source of truth\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:105:- [x] implement one shared live-thread resolver from `panel.lastPayload.dashboard.threads` and use it only in `assignTaskToThread`, `claimTaskForThread`, `heartbeatThread`, `blockTaskForThread`, and `completeTaskForThread`\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:108:- [ ] if an analysis loop finds risk to the current stable version, prioritize containment, revert-friendly isolation, or follow-up hardening before adding new behavior\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:113:- [x] add package ignore or allowlist coverage so loop state, plan logs, and generated VSIX artifacts do not destabilize extension packaging\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:114:- [ ] use commit shapes such as `feat(team-mailbox): ...` and `docs(loop): ...`\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:115:- [ ] avoid sweeping refactors until mailbox behavior is stable\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:120:- mailbox coordination is plan-driven through `codex-loop`\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:122:- team-mode behavior is visibly available but remains opt-in\ntask-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md:123:- existing extension features remain usable without mailbox initialization\npackage.json:4:  \"description\": \"Manage Codex agent threads inside VS Code with search, lifecycle actions, inspector views, and local dashboard integration.\",\npackage.json:35:    \"dashboard\",\npackage.json:54:    \"onCommand:codexAgent.maximizeDashboard\",\npackage.json:78:          \"description\": \"Optional Python executable used to launch the local Codex-Managed-Agent server. Leave empty to auto-detect .venv/bin/python3 or use python3.\"\npackage.json:94:          \"description\": \"Preferred surface to open when the dashboard is first revealed.\"\npackage.json:101:        \"title\": \"Codex-Managed-Agent: Open Dashboard\"\npackage.json:124:        \"command\": \"codexAgent.maximizeDashboard\",\npackage.json:161:          \"name\": \"Dashboard\"\npackage.json:168:          \"name\": \"Dashboard\"\npackage.json:190:          \"command\": \"codexAgent.maximizeDashboard\",\n.codex-loop/prompt.md:8:2. `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md`\n.codex-loop/prompt.md:9:   - treat this as the mailbox-team long-form execution plan\n.codex-loop/prompt.md:21:- Do not expand scope beyond the current mailbox loop track.\n.codex-loop/prompt.md:22:- Prefer the mailbox-team plan before reopening older paused tracks.\n.codex-loop/prompt.md:24:- If `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md` is active, follow it instead of inventing a new plan.\n.codex-loop/prompt.md:30:- The immediate analysis gate for this mailbox track is satisfied; continue using the two-loop review rule instead of forcing every next pass to be analysis-only.\n.codex-loop/prompt.md:31:- When a pass is an analysis loop, explicitly audit legacy thread lifecycle safety, board/tab semantic safety, loop-only cadence impact, task-plan/code alignment, a