: initialize, assign, inspect, recover, and handoff\\n    62\\t- [ ] support worker actions as mailbox events only: claim, heartbeat, blocked, complete\\n    63\\t- [x] attach a result envelope shape to completion events so future automation can inspect outcomes\\n    64\\t- [ ] define stale-lease recovery behavior before adding background reclamation automation\\n    65\\t\\n    66\\t## Supervisor and Worker Action Model\\n    67\\t\\n    68\\tCurrent mailbox action boundaries:\\n    69\\t\\n    70\\t- Supervisor actions are explicit host/dashboard actions: initialize team space, assign a task to a live thread, inspect mailbox-derived team state, recover by re-reading mailbox files on refresh, and receive handoffs through events plus supervisor inbox messages.\\n    71\\t- Worker actions are represented as mailbox state transitions plus append-only events: claim, heartbeat/progress, blocked, and complete.\\n    72\\t- Worker blocked and complete actions also notify the supervisor through `inbox/supervisor.jsonl`.\\n    73\\t- This model does not route work through board tabs and does not replace legacy thread lifecycle state.\\n    74\\t\\n    75\\t## Completion Result Envelope\\n    76\\t\\n    77\\tCompletion events use the same result envelope stored on the task record and sent as the `payload` of `task.completed` events:\\n    78\\t\\n    79\\t- `summary`: non-empty human-readable completion summary.\\n    80\\t- `outputs`: array of produced artifact references or paths.\\n    81\\t- `checks_run`: array of validation commands or checks performed.\\n    82\\t- `open_risks`: array of known residual risks, blockers, or caveats.\\n    83\\t- `next_request`: optional follow-up request for the supervisor.\\n    84\\t\\n    85\\t## Task 4 — Non-Destructive Dashboard Surface\\n    86\\t\\n    87\\t- [x] surface mailbox summary in overview without reshaping existing overview cards\\n    88\\t- [x] expose thread-level team controls only inside bounded surfaces such as the drawer\\n    89\\t- [x] avoid overloading current board tab semantics with team routing semantics\\n    90\\t- [x] make the team surface clearly secondary when mailbox mode is not initialized\\n    91\\t\\n    92\\t## Task 5 — Loop Automation Defaults\\n    15\\t- `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md`\\n    16\\t\\n    17\\t## Current Slice\\n    18\\t\\n    19\\t- [ ] Analysis slice — audit the Task 3 supervisor/worker action-model note against current runtime behavior.\\n    20\\t\\n    21\\t## Next Handoff\\n    22\\t\\n    23\\t- Loop type just completed: execution; the Task 3 supervisor/worker action-model note was added without runtime changes.\\n    24\\t- Keep the mailbox cadence at 1 minute unless the user explicitly overrides it.\\n    25\\t- Current milestone: follow-on track — `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md`.\\n    26\\t- Next slice: run an analysis loop that verifies the note matches initialize, assign, inspect, recover-by-read, handoff, claim, heartbeat, blocked, and complete behavior before deciding whether the supervisor/worker Task 3 checkboxes can be marked complete.\\n    27\\t- Keep the next pass non-destructive: do not change mailbox UI, stale-lease recovery, broader supervisor flow, packaging rules, or board/tab semantics.\\n    28\\t- Do not mark stale-lease recovery complete until behavior is explicitly defined before automation.\\n     1\\t## Loop Type\\n     2\\t- type: execution\\n     3\\t\\n     4\\t## What Changed\\n     5\\t- Added a minimal Task 3 supervisor/worker action-model note to `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md`.\\n     6\\t- Documented the current boundary between supervisor host/dashboard actions and worker mailbox state/event actions.\\n     7\\t- No Task 3 supervisor/worker checkbox was marked complete in this pass.\\n     8\\t- No runtime behavior, UI, stale recovery, packaging rules, or board/tab semantics changed.\\n     9\\t\\n    10\\t## Plan\\n    11\\t- Active plan: `.c