ery, or broader supervisor flow changes.\\n- Keep the closure rule fixed: the resolver slice should close both Task 6 thread-validation checkboxes together, because the resolver is the concrete implementation of the stale-thread rejection outcome.\\n- If the hardening pass finds risk to current stable behavior, pause feature expansion and route the following pass to containment or rollback-friendly isolation.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n.codex-loop/state/logs/tick_20260416_025148.log:41:{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_5\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' task-plans/claude-codex-team-space-task-plan.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n.codex-loop/state/logs/tick_20260416_025148.log:42:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_5\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' task-plans/claude-codex-team-space-task-plan.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# Claude Codex Team Space Task Plan\\n\\n## Priority\\n\\nPriority 3\\n\\n## Objective\\n\\nExpand from Codex-only control into a provider-aware agent team workspace.\\n\\n## Scope\\n\\n- Claude + Codex shared board\\n- provider-aware role separation\\n- collaboration model across providers\\n\\n## Tasks\\n\\n### Task 1 — Provider Abstraction\\n\\n- define provider-neutral thread/task concepts\\n- keep provider-specific actions isolated\\n\\n### Task 2 — Shared Team Surface\\n\\n- decide how Codex and Claude entities coexist in one board or team space\\n- keep visual semantics clear across providers\\n\\n### Task 3 — Role and Ownership Model\\n\\n- define how work is split between providers\\n- avoid pretending provider internals are fully controllable\\n\\n## Constraints\\n\\nOfficial provider plugins do not expose full internal APIs. This phase must be designed as coordination, not total provider control.\\n\\n## Exit Criteria\\n\\n- a realis