[ ] keep related threads linked as part of one larger work plan\\n\\n## Exit Criteria\\n\\n- multiple Codex threads can be used as a coordinated work set\\n- coordination semantics are explicit, not implicit\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n.codex-loop/state/logs/tick_20260416_042007.log:135:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_6\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' .claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# ACTIVE_PLAN\\n\\nTrack Status: active\\n\\n## Milestone Status\\n\\n- [x] Milestone 1 — Architecture Stabilization\\n- [x] Milestone 2 — Board Interaction Quality\\n- [x] Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer\\n- [x] Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability\\n- [x] Milestone 5 — Publishable Product Quality\\n\\n## Current Task Plan\\n\\n- `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md`\\n\\n## Current Slice\\n\\n- [ ] Analysis slice — audit the `appendEvent` envelope guard before broader write-path hardening.\\n\\n## Next Handoff\\n\\n- Loop type just completed: execution; `appendEvent` now guards event envelopes and packaging passed.\\n- Keep the mailbox cadence at 1 minute unless the user explicitly overrides it.\\n- Current milestone: follow-on track — `task-plans/codex-team-mailbox-loop-task-plan.md`.\\n- Next slice: run an analysis loop that verifies valid team events still append, malformed events are rejected, and task/event/inbox id behavior did not drift.\\n- Keep the next pass non-destructive: do not change mailbox UI, stale-lease recovery, broader supervisor flow, packaging rules, or board/tab semantics.\\n- If no drift is found, continue Task 2 with the smallest remaining write-path hardening slice.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n.codex-loop/state/logs/tick_20260416_042007.log:146:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_7\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"find .claude/plans/loloop -maxdepth 1 -t